Interface IInstanceID

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IDataWindow<DATA>, IDoubleFeature, IDoubleWindow, IFeature<FDATA>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataWindow, CachingIterable, DoubleFeature, DoubleWindow, InstanceIdentifiedObject, MemoryCachingLabeledFeatureIterable, SoundClip, SoundRecordingMetaData.SoundClipMetaData

    public interface IInstanceID
    Defines the capability to have a unique run-time instance identifier. It need not be persisted across JVM restarts.
    Author:
    dawood
